Cordillera del Cóndor. The Machinaza plateau, one of the highest-elevation Hollín sandstone plateaus in the Cóndor region. About 500 m west of the Ecuador-Peru international border, near end of trail from Paquisha Alto military post. Bare sandstone substrate, or quartzsite sand derived therefrom, very nutrient-poor. Dwarf scrub vegetation, dominated by shrubs to about 1.5 m tall, with occasional small trees to 4 m tall. Vegetation recovering slowly from an extensive burn about 20 years previously, with charred woody stems in abundance on ground.
